%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20man%20exploited%20a%20glitch%20in%20the%20CIA's%20X%20account%20to%20redirect%20Russian%20informants%20to%20his%20own%20Telegram%20channel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222230%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22CIA%20flag%20made%20using%20computer%20binary%20code.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652faaeabe9edfa8eda3727b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221344%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20flag%20of%20the%20CIA%20made%20using%20computer%20binary%20code.%3Cp%3EGwengoat%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20American%20cybersecurity%20expert%20noticed%20a%20glitch%20on%20the%20CIA's%20X%20account.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EX%20truncated%20a%20CIA%20link%20meant%20for%20Russian%20informants.%C2%A0Kevin%20McSheehan%20claimed%20the%20Telegram%20username.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20he%20exploited%20the%20glitch%20to%20stop%20hostile%20actors%20from%20intercepting%20Western%20intelligence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20American%20cybersecurity%20researcher%20exploited%20a%20glitch%20on%20the%20CIA's%20X%20account%20to%20redirect%20potential%20Russian%20informants%20to%20his%20own%20Telegram%20channel%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Ftechnology-67137773%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20BBC%20News.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20McSheehan%2C%2037%2C%20said%20he%20identified%20and%20exploited%20the%20glitch%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter%2C%20to%20prevent%20any%20hostile%20actors%20from%20capitalizing%20on%20the%20mistake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20saw%20that%20the%20official%20Telegram%20link%20they%20were%20sharing%20could%20be%20hijacked%20%E2%80%94%20and%20my%20biggest%20fear%20was%20that%20a%20country%20like%20Russia%2C%20China%2C%20or%20North%20Korea%20could%20easily%20intercept%20Western%20intelligence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BBC%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20CIA%