n%20Puerto%20Rico%20that%20manufactured%20CD's%20of%20the%20company's%20famed%20software%2C%20by%20selling%20its%20intellectual%20property%20to%20that%20small%20factory.%20Under%20a%20deal%20with%20Puerto%20Rico%2C%20those%20profits%20were%20taxed%20at%20an%20almost%200%25%20rate%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Farticle%2Fthe-irs-decided-to-get-tough-against-microsoft-microsoft-got-tougher%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EProPublica%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20the%20IRS%20says%20that's%20a%20form%20of%20tax%20dodging%20since%20it%20avoided%20mainland%20US%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft's%20case%20is%20not%20new%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%2428.9%20billion%20figure%20is%20the%20end%20result%20of%20an%20historic%2C%20years-long%20audit%20of%20the%20software%20giant's%20taxes%20from%202004%20to%202013.%20As%20Microsoft%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.microsoft.com%2Fon-the-issues%2F2023%2F10%2F11%2Fupdate-irs-audit%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enotes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ealso%20likely%20kicks%20off%20more%20years%20of%20appeals%20and%20hashing%20out%20what%2C%20exactly%2C%20Microsoft%20should%20pay.%20Microsoft%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.microsoft.com%2Fon-the-issues%2F2023%2F10%2F11%2Fupdate-irs-audit%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bdisagrees%20with%20these%20proposed%20adjustments%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20ultimate%20bill%20could%20be%20%2410%20billion%20less%2C%20when%20accounting%20for%20taxes%20paid%20under%20Trump's%202017%20Tax%20Cuts%20and%20Jobs%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20we%20have%20always%20followed%20the%20IRS'%20rules%20and%20paid%20the%20taxes%20we%20owe%20in%20the%20U.S.%20and%20around%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20Goff%2C%20Microsoft's%20corporate%20vice%20president%20for%20worldwide%20tax%20and%20customs%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.microsoft.com%2Fon-the-issues%2F2023%2F10%2F11%2Fupdate-irs-audit%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BMicrosoft%20historically%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20top%20U.S.%20corporate%20income%20taxpayers.%20Since%202004%2C%20we%20have%20paid%20over%20%2467%20billion%20in%20taxes%20to%20the%20U.S.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20it%20means%20for%20other%20tech%20giants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20isn't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-microsoft-avoids-taxes-loopholes-irs-2013-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ealone%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20it's%20impossible%20to%20know%20with%20precision%20just%20how%20prevalent%20the%20practice%20of%20profit%20shifting%2C%20where%20companies%20move%20revenues%20and%20profits%20to%20lower-tax%20regions%2C%20is%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20the%20IRS%20is%20signaling%20is%20that%20they're%20more%20common%20than%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Natasha%20Sarin%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20law%20at%20Yale%20Law%20School%20and%20former%20counselor%20to%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Janet%20Yellen%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20sort%20of%20particularly%20small%20or%20unknown%20types%20of%20corporations%20engaged%20in%20this%20behavior%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarin%2C%20whose%20work%20at%20the%20Treasury%20Department%20focused%20on%20narrowing%20gaps%20between%20taxes%20paid%20and%20owed%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20the%20behemoths%20of%20the%20American%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgabriel-zucman.eu%2Ffiles%2FWZ2022WIDER.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eworking%20paper%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Ludvig%20Wier%2C%20an%20economist%20and%20Head%20of%20Secretariat%20the%20Danish%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%2C%20and%20UC%20Berkeley%20economist%20Gabriel%20Zucman%20found%20that%20the%20share%20of%20corporate%20profits%20recorded%20in%20a%20country%20that%20doesn't%20contain%20the%20company's%20headquarters%20more%20than%20quadrupled%20since%201975.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAccording%20to%20the%20paper%2C%20foreign%20firms%20registered%2016%20times%20as%20much%20value%20in%20profits%20in%20Puerto%20Rico%20as%20wages%20paid%20to%20employees%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%20alone%2C%20the%20authors%20estimate%20that%2C%20globally%2C%20%24969%20billion%20in%20profits%20were%20shifted%20to%20tax%20havens.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20around%20%24165%20billion%20in%20profits%20were%20shifted%2C%20and%20the%20US%20saw%20a%2016%25%20loss%20in%20corporate%20tax%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERich%20and%20large%20corporations%20are%20%26quot%3Bevasion%20advantaged%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20according%20to%20Sarin.%20%26quot%3BThat%20has%20to%20be%20something%20that%20we%20care%20about%2C%20not%20just%20again%20from%20a%20revenue%20perspective%2C%20but%20also%20from%20an%20equity%20perspective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarin%20said%20that%20the%20corporate%20tax%20gap%20%E2%80%94%20the%20gap%20between%20how%20much%20companies%20should%20be%20paying%20and%20actually%20are%20%E2%80%94%20is%20around%20%2440%20billion%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20line%20between%20avoidance%20and%20evasion%20is%20pretty%20blurry%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20to%20know%20until%20the%20IRS%20starts%20to%20be%20able%20to%20undertake%20activities%20like%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Enewly%20resourced%20IRS%20has%20started%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20tax%20evasion%20more%20broadly%20after%20years%20of%20underfunding%2C%20with%20funds%20from%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrsreports.congress.gov%2Fproduct%2Fpdf%2FIN%2FIN11977%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520IRA%2520gave%2520the%2520IRS%2Cdigital%2520assets%2520such%2520as%2520cryptocurrency.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Especifically%20allocated%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20towards%20increased%20enforcement%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20real%20impediment%20to%20the%20kind%20of%20equity%20I%20think%20we%20all%20would%20like%20to%20see%20%E2%80%94or%20many%20of%20us%20would%20like%20to%20see%20in%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20is%20tax%20administration.%20It's%20not%20like%20we%20don't%20know%20the%20size%20or%20shape%20of%20the%20problem%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20like%20we%20don't%20know%20the%20solution%20to%20the%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Sarin%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20solution%20to%20the%20problem%20is%20resourcing%20the%20tax%20administrator%20so%20they%20can%20make%20sure%20that%20those%20types%20of%20inequities%20are%20not%20perpetuated%20by%20the%20behavior%20of%20an%20elite%20few.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorporate-taxes-dodging-irs-enforcement-microsoft-audit-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697623441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F634f5bfd6bd52700191539ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorporate-taxes-dodging-irs-enforcement-microsoft-audit-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20IRS%20says%20Microsoft%20owes%20nearly%20%2429%20billion%20in%20back%20taxes.%20It%20might%20signal%20a%20widespread%20practice.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorporate-taxes-dodging-irs-enforcement-microsoft-audit-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Welcome%20to%20office%20dystopia%2C%20where%20everyday%20work%20can%20feel%20irrelevant%20as%20global%20conflict%20rages%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22man%20looking%20stressed%20in%20a%20messy%20office%5C%22%20charset%3D