C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Millennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%20are%20banking%20on%20an%20inheritance%20from%20their%20boomer%20parents.%20That's%20a%20big%20mistake.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20dollar%20cake%20is%20being%20cut%20up%20by%20old%20and%20wealthy%20people.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529966e6561dd877e7a86e2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBoomers%20are%20rolling%20in%20financial%20assets.%20But%20they%20are%20probably%20going%20to%20spend%20all%20their%20savings%20before%20they%20can%20pass%20anything%20down%20to%20their%20children.%3Cp%3EChelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband's%20grandmother%20turned%2087%2C%20our%20family%20realized%20it%20was%20time%20for%20us%20to%20take%20over%20her%20affairs.%20Grandma%20Sue%20was%20ailing%20and%20recently%20widowed%2C%20so%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fparents-getting-older-how-talk-aging-senior-care-2023-8%5C%22%3Edecided%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20best%20for%20her%20to%20turn%20over%20her%20finances.%20Between%20retirement%20savings%20and%20the%20proceeds%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20her%20house%2C%20she%20had%20about%20%24250%2C000%20in%20assets%20at%20the%20time.%20She%20told%20my%20husband%20that%20he%20would%20inherit%20all%20of%20it.%20On%20the%20face%20of%20it%2C%20Grandma%20Sue's%20generosity%20seemed%20like%20it%20would%20be%20a%20huge%20financial%20help%20for%20our%20family%20since%20the%20money%20was%20just%20about%20enough%20to%20pay%20off%20our%20mortgage.%20But%20my%20husband%20wasn't%20banking%20on%20a%20windfall.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrandma%20Sue%20was%20able%20to%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20assisted%20living%20with%20the%20income%20she%20was%20receiving%20from%20Social%20Security%20and%20the%20income%20on%20her%20savings.%20But%20after%20six%20years%2C%20she%20needed%20round-the-clock%20care%20and%20eventually%20was%20moved%20into%20a%20nursing%20home.%20The%20transition%20was%20tough%20and%20the%20nursing%20home%20wasn't%20cheap%2C%20but%20it%20was%20necessary%20to%20keep%20her%20comfortable.%20Eventually%2C%20Grandma%20Sue%20dipped%20into%20her%20principal%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20bills%2C%20and%20after%20eight%20years%2C%20she%20had%20gone%20through%20the%20majority%20of%20her%20assets.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20she%20qualified%20for%20Medicaid%2C%20which%20covered%20the%20cost%20of%20her%20care.%20But%20that%20left%20my%20husband's%20inheritance%20at%20about%20%242%2C000%2C%20the%20maximum%20amount%20of%20assets%20you%20could%20have%20at%20the%20time%20to%20go%20on%20Medicaid.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20died%2C%20Grandma%20Sue%20left%20the%20most%20common%20form%20of%20inheritance%2C%20called%20an%20accidental%20bequest%2C%20which%20is%20simply%20the%20money%20left%20over%20when%20someone%20dies.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-gift-tax-avoidance-trusts-wealth-planning-rich-inheritance-2023-5%5C%22%3Eintended%20bequest%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20is%20one%20that%20is%20dedicated%20to%20the%20heirs%20and%20set%20aside%20from%20funds%20used%20to%20support%20daily%20living%2C%20often%20through%20a%20trust%20account%20or%20life-insurance%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20happy%20that%20Grandma%20Sue%20had%20enough%20money%20to%20afford%20a%20good%20quality%20of%20life%20%E2%80%94%20she%20was%20able%20to%20get%20the%20kind%20of%20care%20she%20needed%20during%20her%20last%20years.%20That%20said%2C%20%242%2C000%20is%20peanuts%20compared%20to%20the%20roughly%20%24250%2C000%20she%20had%20expected%20to%20pass%20on.%20Instead%20of%20paying%20off%20our%20mortgage%2C%20we%20used%20the%20money%20to%20replace%20our%20dining-room%20windows.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20boomer%20generation%20hits%20their%20twilight%20years%2C%20the%20question%20of%20what%20will%20happen%20to%20their%20money%20has%20become%20a%20source%20of%20fascination%20and%20consternation%20for%20economists%2C%20estate%20planners%2C%20and%20families%20across%20the%20country.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftypical-baby-boomer-net-worth-debt-real-estate-retirement-2021-12%5C%22%3EBoomers%3C%2Fa%3E%20hold%20a%20massive%20amount%20of%20wealth%3A%20The%2055.8%20million%20Americans%20over%2065%2C%20about%2017%25%20of%20the%20population%2C%20hold%20half%20of%20America's%20wealth%20%E2%80%94%20%2496.4%20trillion%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve.%20The%20general%20assumption%20is%20that%20as%20this%20older%20generation%20dies%2C%20that%20money%20will%20trickle%20down%20to%20younger%20generations%20and%20give%20cash-strapped%20families%20a%20leg%20up.%20Consider%20it%20the%20Great%20Boomer%20Wealth%20Transfer%20%E2%80%94%20when%20their%20parents%20or%20grandparents%20die%2C%20millions%20of%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20millennials%2C%20and%20Gen%20Zers%20could%20receive%20a%20financial%20windfall%20that%20will%20help%20them%20catch%20up%20financially.%20But%20it%20isn't%20that%20simple.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeath%2C%20they%20say%2C%20is%20the%20great%20equalizer.%20But%20even%20death%20can't%20offset%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-offices-no-inheritance-plans-wealth-transfer-strategy-2023-6%5C%22%3Ewealth%20inequality%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Most%20of%20the%20money%20held%20by%20America's%20older%20generations%20will%20get%20eaten%20up%20by%20long-term%20care%20and%20end-of-life%20costs%2C%20and%20what%20remains%20will%20mostly%20end%20up%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20other%20already-wealthy%20people.%20Instead%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fmoney%2F2017%2Fdec%2F29%2Fmillennials-set-to-reap-huge-rewards-of-inheritance-boom%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einheritance%20boom%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20most%20Americans%20will%20not%20receive%20a%20vast%20fortune%20to%20ameliorate%20their%20grief.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20boy%20who%20cried%20'wealth%20transfer!'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tale%20of%20great%20intergenerational%20wealth%20transfer%20is%20not%20a%20new%20one.%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%20on%20a%20coming%20inheritance%20wealth%20boom%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F05%2F14%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fwealth-generations.html%3FsearchResultPosition%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F12%2F18%2Farts%2Fdesign%2Fgreat-wealth-transfer-art.html%3FsearchResultPosition%3D3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2019%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2014%2F03%2F16%2Fmagazine%2Fbaby-boomers-inheritance.html%3FsearchResultPosition%3D33%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2014%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Fslideshow%2F2008%2F03%2F18%2Fbusiness%2F0318-FAMILY_index.html%3FsearchResultPosition%3D49%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2008%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1999%2F07%2F29%2Fgarden%2Fand-the-meek-shall-inherit-nothing.html%3FsearchResultPosition%3D12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1999%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20story%20is%20simple%20enough%3A%20The%20very%20conservative%20and%20responsible%20%26quot%3Bsilent%20generation%26quot%3B%20would%20be%20leaving%20vast%20sums%20of%20money%20to%20their%20baby-boomer%20progeny%20(and%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20too%2C%20because%20those%20boomers%20couldn't%20save%20worth%20a%20damn).%20And%20now%20the%20boomers%20have%20more%20assets%20than%20even%20they%20can%20spend%2C%20so%20they%20soon%20will%20be%20passing%20on%20those%20funds%20to%20their%20wealth-strapped%20Gen%20Xer%20and%20millennial%20progeny.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20is%20this%20Great%20Wealth%20Transfer%20going%20to%20happen%3F%20Are%20our%20parents%20sitting%20on%20millions%20that%20they%20haven't%20told%20us%20about%3F%20Will%20we%20soon%20see%20a%20life-changing%20jump%20in%20younger%20generations'%20net%20worth%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20past%20is%20any%20indication%2C%20younger%20generations%20shouldn't%20get%20their%20hopes%20up.%20In%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw16840%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202011%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Edward%20Wolff%20of%20New%20York%20University%20and%20Maury%20Gittleman%20of%20the%20US%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20looked%20at%20data%20from%201989%20to%202007%20to%20see%20whether%20there%20was%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20Great%20Wealth%20Transfer.%20The%20researchers%20found%20that%20the%20number%20of%20households%20reporting%20an%20inheritance%20actually%20fell%20by%202.5%20percentage%20points%20during%20that%20time%20period.%20Wolff%20and%20Gittleman%20did%20find%20that%20inheritances%20can%20reduce%20inequality%20a%20bit%20at%20the%20margins.%20A%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20%E2%80%94%20typically%20left%20by%20accidental%20bequest%20%E2%80%94%20can%20make%20a%20big%20difference%20to%20the%20financial%20well-being%20of%20people%20at%20lower-income%20levels.%20But%20the%20bulk%20of%20inheritances%20were%20distributed%20in%20predictable%20ways%3A%20The%20rich%20got%20richer%C2%A0and%20very%20little%20trickled%20down%20to%20the%20majority%20of%20boomers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20baby%20boom%20generation%20was%20reaching%20'prime'%20inheritance%20age%20and%20the%20wealth%20of%20their%20parents%20was%20the%20highest%20in%20history%20for%20that%20age%20group%2C%20wealth%20transfers%20were%20less%20important%20in%20accounting%20for%20current%20net%20worth%20in%202007%20than%20in%201989%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20concluded.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20more%20people%20were%20building%20wealth%20through%20means%20other%20than%20an%20inheritance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20bulk%20of%20inheritances%20were%20distributed%20in%20predictable%20ways%3A%20The%20rich%20got%20richer%C2%A0and%20very%20little%20trickled%20down%20to%20the%20majority%20of%20boomers.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20while%20the%20total%20assets%20held%20by%20boomers%20is%20a%20lot%2C%20most%20of%20that%20is%20held%20by%20a%20small%20number%20of%20people.%20Many%20of%20the%20nation's%20wealthiest%20individuals%20(such%20as%20the%20billionaires%20Michael%20Bloomberg%2C%20Warren%20Buffett%2C%20Larry%20Ellison%2C%20and%20Bill%20Gates)%20are%20in%20this%20demographic%20%E2%80%94%20and%20their%20wealth%20isn't%20about%20to%20trickle%20down%20to%20everyone.%20The%20median%20net%20worth%20of%20people%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2065%20and%2074%20was%20%24266%2C400%20as%20of%202019%2C%20according%20to%20Federal%20Reserve%20data%20%E2%80%94%20not%20much%20higher%20than%20the%20average%20net%20worth%20for%20other%20age%20demographics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20much%20like%20the%20rest%20of%20our%20economy%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20how%20that%20wealth%20will%20be%20passed%20down%2C%20there%20is%20a%20clear%20separation%20between%20the%20haves%20and%20have-nots.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Feconres%2Fnotes%2Ffeds-notes%2Fwealth-and-income-concentration-in-the-scf-20200928.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202019%20study%20by%20researchers%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%2C%20families%20in%20the%20wealthiest%201%25%20of%20Americans%20who%20said%20they%20received%20an%20inheritance%20over%20the%20prior%20three%20years%20reported%20getting%20an%20average%20of%20%24719%2C000%20passed%20down%2C%20and%20those%20who%20expected%20to%20receive%20an%20inheritance%20in%20the%20future%20guessed%20they%20would%20receive%20an%20average%20of%20%24941%2C000.%20By%20contrast%2C%20people%20in%20the%20bottom%2050%25%20of%20the%20wealth-distribution%20scale%20who%20received%20an%20inheritance%20said%20they%20got%20%249%2C700%20on%20average%2C%20and%20those%20who%20expected%20to%20get%20money%20passed%20down%20in%20the%20future%20estimated%20they%20would%20get%20%2429%2C400%20on%20average.%20Even%20for%20families%20with%20incomes%20in%20the%2051%25%20to%2090%25%20range%20of%20earners%2C%20the%20average%20inheritance%20was%20%2446%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20hardly%20life-changing%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20lot%20more%20wealth%20out%20there%2C%20and%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20in%20the%20age%20groups%20likely%20to%20die%20soon%2C%26quot%3B%20Isabel%20Sawhill%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20told%20me.%C2%A0%20But%2C%20she%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20getting%20inherited%20by%20people%20who%20don't%20need%20it%20very%20much.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20odds%20of%20getting%20any%20of%20that%20wealth%20passed%20down%20are%20slim.%20Researchers%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbudgetmodel.wharton.upenn.edu%2Fissues%2F2021%2F7%2F16%2Finheritances-by-age-and-income-group%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Pennsylvania%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20the%20likelihood%20of%20someone%20receiving%20an%20inheritance%20in%20any%20given%20five-year%20period%20is%207.4%25.%20That%20likelihood%20increases%20the%20richer%20you%20are.%20People%20in%20the%20top%205%25%20of%20earners%20had%20an%2011.2%25%20chance%20of%20receiving%20an%20inheritance%20in%20a%20five-year%20period.%20The%20Penn%20researchers%20initially%20found%20that%20the%20median%20inheritance%20among%20all%20survey%20participants%20was%20just%20over%20%2412%2C000%2C%20but%20that%20included%20people%20who%20reported%20zero%20inheritance.%20When%20the%20researchers%20calculated%20the%20median%20inheritance%20among%20people%20who%20actually%20received%20one%2C%20the%20number%20was%20quite%20a%20bit%20higher%3A%20%24183%2C914.%20And%20families%20in%20the%20top%205%25%20who%20received%20an%20inheritance%20far%20outpaced%20the%20rest%20%E2%80%94%20receiving%20a%20median%20of%20%24424%2C343.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Fed%20research%20and%20the%20Penn%20survey%20seem%20to%20point%20to%20the%20same%20idea%3A%20If%20your%20family%20is%20already%20wealthy%2C%20there's%20a%20good%20chance%20you'll%20get%20an%20inheritance%20and%20it'll%20be%20a%20big%20one.%20Everyone%20else%3F%20Good%20luck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20cost%20of%20long-term%20care%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20among%20Americans%20who%20are%20lucky%20enough%20to%20expect%20an%20inheritance%2C%20there%20is%20a%20good%20chance%20that%20their%20boomer%20parents%20may%20not%20have%20as%20much%20to%20pass%20down%20as%20they%20think.%20Our%20experience%20with%20Grandma%20Sue's%20end-of-life%20care%20is%20not%20atypical%3A%20Healthcare%20costs%20will%20crack%20any%20nest%20egg%2C%20and%20long-term%20care%20will%20crush%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20most%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.genworth.com%2Faging-and-you%2Ffinances%2Fcost-of-care%2Fcost-of-care-trends-and-insights.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20cost%20of%20elder%20care%2C%20Genworth%2C%20an%20insurance%20company%20that%20sells%20long-term-care%20policies%2C%20found%20that%20the%20average%20monthly%20cost%20of%20a%2040-hour-a-week%20home%20health%20aide%20was%20about%20%244%2C600.%20For%20an%20assisted-living%20facility%2C%20the%20average%20monthly%20cost%20was%20%244%2C500%2C%20while%20a%20private%20room%20in%20a%20nursing%20home%20would%20set%20you%20back%20more%20than%20%249%2C000.%20Almost%20none%20of%20this%20is%20covered%20by%20Medicare.%20The%20Kaiser%20Family%20Foundation%20reports%20that%20Medicaid%20covers%2062%25%20of%20long-term-care%20residents%2C%20but%20unless%20they%20are%20already%20poor%2C%20people%20have%20to%20spend%20down%20their%20assets%20in%20order%20to%20qualify.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20boomers%20age%2C%20costs%20are%20likely%20to%20go%20up%20with%20rising%20demand%20for%20care%20leading%20to%20higher%20wages%20for%20caregivers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20higher%20costs.%20While%20life%20expectancy%20ticked%20down%20as%20a%20result%20of%20COVID-19%2C%20it's%20unclear%20if%20that%20is%20a%20permanent%20trend%20or%20a%20short-term%20blip.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3E'My%20kids%20can%20have%20whatever%20is%20left%20over%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20living%20my%20life%20in%20such%20a%20way%20as%20to%20try%20and%20preserve%20resources%20for%20them.'%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20as%20if%20healthcare%20is%20the%20only%20cost%20for%20older%20Americans.%20Retired%20people%20spend%20years%20building%20up%20a%20nest%20egg%2C%20and%20when%20they're%20finally%20freed%20from%20the%20nine-to-five%20grind%2C%20they%20want%20to%20spend%20their%20money.%20That's%20why%20we%20build%20savings%2C%20after%20all.%20In%20June%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbusiness.bofa.com%2Fen-us%2Fcontent%2Fbank-of-america-institute%2Feconomic-insights%2Fconsumer-checkpoint-june-2023.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBank%20of%20America%20Institute's%20Consumer%20Checkpoint%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20older%20Bank%20of%20America%20cardholders%20spent%20more%20money%20in%20the%20past%20year%20than%20younger%20ones.%20And%20data%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor's%20survey%20of%20consumer%20expenditures%20shows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-spending-net-worth-us-economy-recession-2023-10%5C%22%3Espending%20by%20older%20households%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20increased%20by%2034.5%25%20since%201982%2C%20while%20it's%20increased%20by%2016.5%25%20for%20younger%20generations%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20wealth%20creators%20are%20primarily%20focused%20on%20their%20own%20financial%20security%2C%20so%20the%20concept%20of%20inheritance%20planning%20naturally%20becomes%20a%20much%20lower%20priority%2C%26quot%3B%20Joseph%20Smith%2C%20a%20wealth%20management%20advisor%20with%20Northwestern%20Mutual%20who%20often%20works%20with%20clients%20planning%20to%20give%20or%20receive%20an%20inheritance%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey'll%20often%20say%3A%20'My%20kids%20can%20have%20whatever%20is%20left%20over%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20living%20my%20life%20in%20such%20a%20way%20as%20to%20try%20and%20preserve%20resources%20for%20them!'%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20also%20worked%20with%20people%20who%20expect%20an%20inheritance%20but%20don't%20receive%20one%2C%20which%20happens%20more%20often%20than%20you'd%20think.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20often%20taboo%20to%20ask%20a%20parent%20about%20how%20much%20money%20they%20have%20or%20what%20their%20plans%20are%20for%20when%20they%20die%2C%20and%20heirs%20can%20make%20poor%20assumptions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Those%20assumptions%20can%20include%20underestimating%20the%20costs%20of%20long-term%20care%20or%20how%20much%20their%20parents%20actually%20have.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.northwesternmutual.com%2Flife-and-money%2Flegacy-planning-starting-the-conversation-with-your-heirs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENorthwestern%20Mutual's%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20found%20that%20nearly%20a%20quarter%20of%20wealth%20creators%20and%20almost%20one-in-three%20heirs%20haven't%20discussed%20the%20benefactor's%20will%20or%20legacy%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20boomer%20spending%20does%20keep%20that%20wealth%20churning%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20that's%20any%20better%20than%20leaving%20more%20money%20to%20their%20children.%20Getting%20a%20large%20lump%20sum%20of%20money%20may%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20or%20start%20a%20business%2C%20and%20some%20hopeful%20heirs%20may%20lose%20that%20opportunity%20if%20they%20don't%20receive%20an%20inheritance.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20do%20we%20love%20this%20story%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20been%20talking%20about%20the%20coming%20Great%20Wealth%20Transfer%20for%20at%20least%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20century.%20And%20it's%20nice%20to%20think%20that%20many%20of%20us%20are%20heading%20for%20a%20financial%20windfall%20that%20will%20solve%20our%20economic%20problems.%20But%20unless%20your%20family%20is%20already%20very%20wealthy%2C%20the%20likelihood%20that%20will%20happen%20to%20you%20is%20small.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20possible%20reason%20for%20the%20continued%20wealth-transfer%20myth%20is%20that%20it%20encourages%20people%20to%20oppose%20estate%20taxation%2C%20which%20would%20go%20a%20long%20way%20toward%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fwealth-inheritance-and-social-mobility%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereducing%20income%20inequality%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20all%2C%20if%20you%20think%20you're%20getting%20a%20large%20inheritance%2C%20you%20probably%20don't%20want%20that%20to%20be%20shrunk%20by%20taxes.%20And%20the%20current%20tax%20exemptions%20are%20huge%3A%20Estates%20of%20less%20than%20%2412.9%20million%20are%20free%20from%20any%20taxation.%20Of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fmmwr%2Fvolumes%2F71%2Fwr%2Fmm7117e1.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3.5%20million%20people%20who%20died%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%2C%20the%20IRS%20received%20just%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irs.gov%2Fstatistics%2Fsoi-tax-stats-estate-tax-filing-year-tables%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E6%2C000%20estate-tax%20filings%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20means%20only%200.17%25%20of%20estates%20were%20taxed%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20every%20trust-fund%20baby%20out%20there%2C%20there%20are%20thousands%20of%20people%20who%20would%20be%20better%20off%20with%20an%20extra%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20to%20pay%20down%20credit-card%20debt%2C%20cover%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20down%20payment%20on%20a%20home%2C%20or%20put%20toward%20retirement.%20But%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20all%20the%20wealth%20boomers%20are%20sitting%20on%20probably%20won't%20end%20up%20fixing%20our%20collective%20financial%20problems.%20On%20a%20national%20scale%2C%20the%20death%20of%20boomers%20is%20unlikely%20to%20shift%20the%20current%20breakdown%20of%20wealth%20inequality%20or%20cause%20a%20sudden%20economic%20boom.%20Some%20people%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20money.%20Everyone%20will%20die.%20This%20doesn't%20translate%20into%20something%20that%20will%20change%20the%20lives%20of%20most%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fann-c-logue%5C%22%3EAnn%20Logue%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20writer%20specializing%20in%20business%20and%20finance.%20Her%20most%20recent%20book%20is%20%26quot%3BOptions%20Trading.%26quot%3B%20She%20lives%20in%20Chicago.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-wealth-transfer-myth-dont-count-on-inheritance-estate-planning-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697622302000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529969d55f52b01b35f7630%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-wealth-transfer-myth-dont-count-on-inheritance-estate-planning-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Boomers%20hold%20half%20of%20America's%20wealth%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they're%20going%20to%20spend%20it%20on%20themselves%20before%20their%20kids%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20inherit%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ann%20C.%20Logue)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2