b1100504.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20trend%20emerged%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20clip%20of%20hosts%20on%20the%20New%20Zealand%20radio%20station%20FVHZM%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40fvhzm%2Fvideo%2F7261005803098737921%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewent%20viral%20on%20TikTok%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20clip%20was%20of%20the%20show's%20segment%20in%20which%20female%20listeners%20call%20in%20to%20justify%20their%20big%20purchases%20with%20the%20excuse%20of%20%26quot%3Bgirl%20maths.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TikTok%20video%20spurred%20a%20wave%20of%20videos%20in%20response%20with%20women%20discussing%20how%20they%20justified%20spending%20that%20could%20be%20viewed%20as%20impractical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20girl%20math%20is%20a%20negative%20trend%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESeemingly%20lighthearted%2C%20the%20hashtag%20plays%20into%20a%20damaging%20stereotype%20that%20women%20are%20bad%20at%20math.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Institute%20for%20Fiscal%20Studies%20found%20in%20the%20UK%20in%202018%20that%20more%20girls%20than%20boys%20received%20A-level%20certifications%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0but%20female%20students%20made%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fifs.org.uk%2Farticles%2Fwhy-dont-more-girls-study-maths-and-physics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eonly%2039%25%20of%20math%20A-level%20results%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%2022%25%20of%20physics%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20imbalance%20in%20women%20studying%20math-based%20topics%20is%20reiterated%20in%20higher%20education.%20UCAS%20data%20shows%20non-male%20students%20%E2%80%93%20participants%20who%20identified%20as%20women%20or%20nonbinary%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0only%20made%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stemwomen.com%2Fwomen-in-stem-statistics-progress-and-challenges%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E31%25%20of%20students%20studying%20mathematics%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20universities%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20historically%2C%20women%20have%20excelled%20in%20mathematics.%20Caroline%20Criado%20Perez%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BInvisible%20Women%2C%26quot%3B%20highlights%20Dainan%20Tamina%2C%20a%20female%20mathematician%20who%20solved%20a%20complex%20problem%20that%20had%20eluded%20mathematicians%20for%20centuries%20in%201997.%20Shakuntala%20Devi%20holds%20a%20world%20record%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F07%2F31%2Fmovies%2Fshakuntala-devi-movie.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eperforming%20the%20%26quot%3Bfastest%20human%20computation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20got%20evidence%20of%20female%20mathematicians%20solving%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20greatest%20problems%2C%20yet%20%23girlmath%20perpetuates%20the%20belief%20women%20just%20aren't%20mathsy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGirl%20math%20doubles%20down%20on%20gendering%20lavish%20spending%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%23girlmath%20trend%20focuses%20on%20%26quot%3Bfeminine%26quot%3B%20spending%20habits%20as%20lavish%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0another%20common%20stereotype%20of%20women%20and%20money%20management.%20A%20Guardian%20report%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fmoney%2F2018%2Fmar%2F10%2Fmedia-stereotype-women-in-financial-coverage-study-finds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E65%25%20of%20financial%20articles%20directed%20at%20women%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20characterized%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Bsplurgers%26quot%3B%20and%20sought%20to%20teach%20them%20how%20to%20rein%20in%20their%20wild%20feminine%20spending%20tendencies.%20This%20content%20usually%20revolves%20around%20childlike%20images%20of%20piggy%20banks%2C%20or%20simplified%20techniques%20of%20stretching%20budgets%20ever%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStereotyping%20women%20as%20having%20poor%20maths%20skills%20has%20a%20direct%20correlation%20with%20an%20unwillingness%20to%20engage%20with%20finances.%20A%202021%20study%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20Economic%20Behavior%20and%20Organization%20suggests%20the%20stereotype%20that%20women%20are%20less%20financially%20literate%20increases%20their%20anxiety%20around%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202021%20study%20of%202%2C400%20American%20adults%20making%20an%20annual%20income%20of%20%2450%2C000%20or%20more%2C%20Fidelity%20found%20only%20a%20third%20of%20female%20participants%20said%20they%20were%20confident%20in%20their%20ability%20to%20invest.%20Even%20though%20a%20Fidelity%20analysis%20of%205%20million%20of%20its%20customers%20from%20a%20recent%2010-year%20period%20found%20that%20women%20actually%20slightly%20outperformed%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThen%20came%20'boy%20math'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20%23girlmath%2C%20the%20trend%20%23boymath%20has%20also%20started%20to%20emerge.%20This%20trend%20appears%20to%20balance%20the%20perceived%20financial%20illiteracy%20scales.%20%26quot%3BBoy%20math%26quot%3B%20was%20defined%20by%20one%20X%20user%20as%20%26quot%3Bpaying%20%2444%20billion%20for%20a%20%2425%20billion%20company%20and%2C%20through%20business%20smarts%20and%20entrepreneurial%20know-how%2C%20turning%20it%20into%20an%20%248.8%20billion%20company.%26quot%3B%20The%20tweet%20alludes%20to%20Elon%20Musk's%20acquisition%20of%20Twitter%2C%20which%20he%20rebranded%20to%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20worth%20noting%20that%20the%20boy-math%20trend%20seems%20to%20illustrate%20illogical%20male%20behavior%20in%20a%20more%20general%20sense%2C%20whereas%20girl%20math%20is%20pointedly%20financial.%20When%20the%20trend's%20negative%20spotlight%20is%20directed%20toward%20men%2C%20it%20avoids%20conflating%20men%20with%20poor%20financial%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWomen's%20financial%20literacy%20is%20an%20important%20issue%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20girl-math%20trend%20brings%20women's%20financial%20literacy%20and%20investing%20into%20the%20limelight.%20Though%20the%20trend%20itself%20perpetuates%20negative%20stereotypes%2C%20it%20opens%20up%20discussions%20around%20gender%20and%20financial%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20do%20women%20cede%20financial%20responsibility%20to%20their%20male%20counterparts%3F%20Why%20do%20women%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2Fselect%2Fwhy-women-dont-save-as-much-as-men%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esave%20less%20on%20average%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Most%20of%20these%20debates%20boil%20down%20to%20the%20gender%20pay%20gap%20and%20continued%20systemic%20misogyny.%20So%2C%20while%20TikTok%20trends%20like%20%23girlmath%20may%20seem%20funny%20and%20fleeting%2C%20the%20stereotypes%20and%20systems%20they%20play%20into%20are%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EZoe%20Burt%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20financial%20content%20specialist%20for%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.femaleinvest.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EFemale%20Invest%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20Burt%20is%20in%20charge%20of%20creating%20and%20presenting%20educational%20and%20inspirational%20webinars%2C%20video%20and%20written%20content%20for%20the%20UK%20and%20global%20audiences%20of%20Female%20Invest%2C%20on%20topics%20including%20investment%20funds%2C%20ISAs%2C%20pensions%20and%20property%20investment.%20She%20leads%20the%20platform's%20UK%20and%20global%20weekly%20market%20news%20roundup%20in%20podcast%2C%20video%2C%20and%20written%20format.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrior%20to%20working%20for%20Female%20Invest%2C%20Burt%20worked%20as%20a%20Wealth%20Advisor%20for%20deVere%20Italia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-girl-math-toxic-tiktok-trend-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697620244000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65295e236561dd877e7a09d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-girl-math-toxic-tiktok-trend-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20financial-content%20specialist%20breaks%20down%20why%20the%20TikTok%20trend%20%23girlmath%20is%20damaging%20to%20women's%20financial%20well-being.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Zoe%20Burt)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-girl-math-toxic-tiktok-trend-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20an%20extrovert%20who%20realized%20working%20remotely%20was%20bad%20for%20my%20mental%20health.%20These%204%20things%20help%20me%20combat%20loneliness.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20woman%20works%20on%20a%20laptop%20while%20sitting%20in%20the%20grass%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b6ced076558a00189d26fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMelissa%20Petro.%3Cp%3EMelissa%20Petro%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMelissa%20Petro%20is%20a%20freelance%20writer%20who%20considers%20herself%20an%20extrovert.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETo%20combat%20loneliness%2C%20she%20works%20daily%20from%20a%20caf%C3%A9%20near%20her%20children's%20school.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20also%20leans%20on%20other%20writers%20and%20online%20communities%20for%20support%20and%20socialization.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20worked%20an%20office%20job%20at%20the%20start%20of%20my%20career%2C%20I%20took%20the%20engaging%20conversations%20I%20had%20with%20my%20coworkers%20for%20granted.%20I%20was%20constantly%20interacting%20with%20other%20people%20and%20felt%20compelled%20to%20collaborate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20years%20I%20taught%20art%20to%20elementary-school%20kids%20tapped%20into%20my%20talkative%20and%20outgoing%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20a%20full-time%20stay-at-home%20parent%2C%20I%20rarely%20stayed%20at%20home.%20My%20kids%20and%20I%20were%20always%20at%20the%20busiest%20of%20playgrounds%2C%20where%20I%20naturally%20gravitated%20toward%20other%20gregarious%20moms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20realize%20how%20much%20of%20an%20extrovert%20I%20was%20until%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffreelance-writer-failed-went-back-full-time-job-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etransitioned%20to%20freelancing%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%202011.%20Writing%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20is%20a%20solitary%20endeavor.%20Focused%20on%20an%20assignment%2C%20I%20can%20go%20for%20days%20without%20interacting%20with%20others%20professionally%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20I've%20learned%20is%20not%20so%20good%20for%20my%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I'm%20not%20alone%20in%20feeling%20alone%3A%20Too%20much%20time%20spent%20turned%20inward%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fhow-social-isolation-affects-mental-health%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esocial%20isolation%20can%20lead%20to%20anxiety%2C%20stress%2C%20and%20cognitive%20decline%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20four%20ways%20I%20stave%20off%20my%20loneliness%20while%20working%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20I%20go%20to%20a%20caf%C3%A9%20every%20day%20instead%20of%20working%20from%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20as%20long%20as%20I've%20worked%20from%20home%2C%20I've%20rarely%20worked%20from%20my%20actual%20house.%20I%20know%20that%20if%20I%20did%2C%20instead%20of%20looking%20at%20my%20computer%20screen%2C%20I'd%20be%20studying%20the%20sink%20full%20of%20dishes%20needing%20to%20be%20washed%2C%20the%20bins%20of%20toys%20begging%20to%20be%20organized%2C%20or%20the%20stationary%20bike%20in%20the%20corner%20collecting%20dust%20%E2%80%94%20basically%20anything%20other%20than%20my%20next%20assignment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20caf%C3%A9%20near%20my%20kids'%20school%20offers%20endless%20inspiration%20instead%20of%20distractions.%20After%20drop-off%2C%20I%20set%20up%20shop%20in%20the%20same%20corner%20every%20day%2C%20so%20I%20can%20periodically%20interact%20with%20the%20staff%2C%20other%20regulars%2C%20and%20even%20strangers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%2420%20or%20so%20I%20spend%20each%20day%20on%20coffee%20and%20food%20is%20well%20worth%20it%2C%20because%20the%20food%20is%20delicious%20and%20the%20environment%20gets%20me%20in%20the%20mood%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOff-the-cuff%20conversations%20I%20have%20in%20the%20caf%C3%A9%20don't%20just%20entertain%20me%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-baristas-feel-when-remote-workers-camp-coffee-shop-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethey%20can%20inspire%20my%20work%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20I%20find%20what's%20going%20on%20around%20me%20distracting%20or%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20bothered%2C%20I%20just%20throw%20on%20a%20pair%20of%20headphones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20I%20have%20a%20close-knit%20writing%20group%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20barista%20may%20be%20one%20of%20my%20favorite%20people%20to%20talk%20to%20about%20feminist%20politics%2C%20but%20she%20doesn't%20always%20get%20the%20latest%20joke%20aimed%20at%20journalists%2C%20and%20she%20can't%20necessarily%20help%20me%20word%20an%20email%20to%20my%20editor%20or%20advise%20me%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fdos-donts-of-haggling-negotiate-better-price-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20to%20negotiate%20a%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20where%20my%20writers%20group%20comes%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20little%20over%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20writer%20I%20met%20online%20invited%20me%20to%20join%20what%20has%20evolved%20into%20a%20vibrant%20WhatsApp%20group%20of%20freelance%20writers%20and%20authors%3A%20a%20half%20dozen%20other%20successful%20women%20who%20I%20can%20turn%20to%20for%20all%20things%20media-related%2C%20from%20a%20funny%20meme%20to%20meaningful%2C%20constructive%20feedback%20on%20a%20pitch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20members%20of%20my%20writing%20group%20are%20like%20coworkers%2C%20only%20better%20because%20it's%20a%20chosen%20circle%20of%20professionals.%20These%20are%20folks%20I%20know%20I%20can%20trust.%20They%20take%20a%20genuine%20interest%20in%20my%20work%20and%20my%20career%2C%20and%20%E2%80%94%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fintrovert-vs-extrovert%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eextroverts%20are%20motivated%20by%20motivating%20others%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20I%20gladly%20return%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20I'm%20a%20part%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20virtual%20communities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20my%20WhatsApp%20group%2C%20I'm%20active%20in%20a%20handful%20of%20other%20online%20groups.%20It%20can't%20replace%20IRL%20interactions%2C%20but%20social%20media%20is%20a%20great%20way%20to%20connect%20with%20like-minded%20people%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0747563214003896%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eespecially%20for%20extroverts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20have%20a%20question%20related%20to%20my%20kid%2C%20for%20example%2C%20I%20can%20turn%20to%20one%20of%20the%20many%20Facebook%20groups%20I'm%20a%20part%20of%20for%20parents%20of%20children%20with%20special%20needs.%20If%20I'm%20just%20looking%20for%20a%20dopamine%20hit%2C%20I%20might%20surf%20over%20to%20my%20%26quot%3BBuy%20Nothing%26quot%3B%20group%20and%20see%20what's%20there%20to%20score.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnections%20made%20over%20social%20media%20can%20cross%20over%20into%20real%20life%2C%20too.%20Fans%20of%20my%20writing%20have%20become%20students.%20One%20mom%20I%20first%20met%20in%20a%20Facebook%20group%20now%20sends%20her%20child%20to%20my%20son's%20therapeutic%20school.%20Before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Ficonaccidental%2F%3Fhl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELyn%20Slater%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20I%20ever%20met%20in%20person%2C%20we%20followed%20each%20other%20on%20Instagram.%20I%20love%20that%20the%20neighbor%20who%20gifts%20me%20a%20Crock-Pot%20from%20the%20%26quot%3BBuy%20Nothing%26quot%3B%20group%20might%20become%20my%20next%20best%20friend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20I%20have%20steady%2C%20long-term%20clients%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20that%20saying%20an%20employer%20feels%20like%20family%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-your-employer-doesnt-care-about-you-2016-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecan%20be%20a%20huge%20red%20flag%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20at%20my%20last%20in-person%20job%2C%20my%20relationships%20went%20deeper%20than%20office%20banter%20and%20watercooler%20gossip.%20They%20saw%20me%20through%20intensely%20personal%20experiences.%20I%20made%20lifelong%20friends%2C%20and%20my%20boss%20even%20officiated%20my%20wedding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20wouldn't%20say%20I've%20developed%20such%20close%20connections%20at%20any%20other%20employer%2C%20I%20do%20appreciate%20that%20as%20a%20freelance%20writer%2C%20I'm%20part%20of%20an%20industry%20that%20feels%20like%20a%20loose%20community%20of%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20never%20met%20some%20of%20the%20people%20I've%20worked%20with%20%E2%80%94%20I%20haven't%20so%20much%20as%20heard%20some%20of%20their%20names%20spoken%20aloud%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I've%20watched%20their%20careers%20evolve%2C%20as%20I%20imagine%20they've%20witnessed%20mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20cultivating%20long-term%20clients%2C%20it's%20about%20more%20than%20just%20making%20friends%3A%20Working%20together%20is%20easier%20because%20of%20the%20strong%2C%20collaborative%20relationships%20we've%20built.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20I%20understand%20their%20needs%20an