f682cbe9edfa8eda36172%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funrwa-gaza-shelter-school-israel-bombed-coordinates-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20least%20six%20people%20died%20after%20the%20school%20was%20hit%2C%20with%20dozens%20more%20injured%20by%20the%20blast%2C%20said%20UNRWA%20Commissioner-General%20Philippe%20Lazzarini.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40insider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funrwa-gaza-shelter-school-israel-bombed-coordinates-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Is%20Islamic%20Jihad%20Group%2C%20Blamed%20By%20Israel%20For%20Gaza%20Hospital%20Bombing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20massive%20explosion%20ripped%20through%20a%20hospital%20in%20Gaza%2C%20killing%20at%20least%20500%20people%20on%20Tuesday.%20The%20incident%20sparked%20global%20outrage%20and%20demonstrations%20in%20several%20Muslim-majority%20countries.%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%20exchanged%20blame%20for%20the%20incident%2C%20which%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20denounced%20while%20en%20route%20to%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Israeli%20army%20pinned%20the%20blame%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bmisfired%20rocket%26quot%3B%20by%20Palestine's%20Islamic%20Jihad%20group%2C%20the%20Hamas-run%20Gaza%20health%20ministry%20says%20Israel%20was%20behind%20the%20bombing%20of%20the%20Al-Ahli%20Arabi%20Baptist%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20is%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20group%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Beginnings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EDesignated%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20by%20the%20US%20State%20Department%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Islamic%20Jihad%20(PIJ)%2C%20an%20ally%20of%20Hamas%2C%20violently%20opposes%20the%20existence%20of%20Israel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20group's%20founders%2C%20Fathi%20Shaqaqi%20and%20Abd%20al-Aziz%20Awda%2C%20were%20students%20in%20Egypt%20and%20members%20of%20the%20Egyptian%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%2C%20a%20Sunni%20Islamist%20social%20movement%20founded%20by%20Hassan%20al-Banna%20in%201928.%20Sometime%20in%20the%20late%201970s%20the%20two%20felt%20that%20the%20Brotherhood%20was%20not%20fully%20committed%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20cause.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETaking%20inspiration%20from%20Ayatollah%20Ruhollah%20Khomeini-led%20Iranian%20revolution%2C%20Shaqaqi%20and%20Awda%20created%20an%20offshoot%20group%20with%20the%20sole%20objective%20of%20militant%20destruction%20of%20the%20Israeli%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201981%2C%20the%20Egyptian%20government%20exiled%20PIJ%2C%20which%20had%20split%20from%20the%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%2C%20to%20Gaza%20after%20the%20assassination%20of%20President%20Anwar%20Sadat%20in%201981.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOperations%20In%20Gaza%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20PIJ%20functions%20as%20a%20decentralised%2C%20compartmentalised%20organisation%20that%20typically%20prioritises%20attacking%20Israel%2C%20while%20avoiding%20the%20prominent%20social%2C%20welfare%2C%20and%20political%20roles%20played%20by%20other%20Islamic%20extremist%20groups%20in%20the%20region%20like%20Hamas%2C%20Fatah%2C%20or%20even%20the%20Lebanon-based%20Iran-backed%20group%20Hezbollah.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETheir%20first%20successful%20strike%20is%20thought%20to%20have%20been%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20killing%20of%20an%20Israeli%20military%20police%20captain%20in%20August%201987%2C%20a%20few%20months%20before%20the%20first%20Palestinian%20intifada.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20killed%20an%20Israeli%20military%20police%20captain%20just%20a%20few%20months%20before%20the%20start%20of%20the%20First%20Intifada%20in%201987.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20year%2C%20they%20were%20expelled%20to%20Lebanon%20where%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20built%20a%20strong%20relationship%20with%20Hezbollah%20and%20even%20received%20arms%20training%20from%20Iranian%20Revolutionary%20Guards.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20Shaqaqi%20established%20the%20group's%20official%20headquarters%20in%20Syria's%20Damascus%20where%20they%20continue%20to%20operate%20to%20this%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERelationship%20With%20Hamas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20does%20not%20carry%20out%20any%20form%20of%20social%20service%20in%20Gaza%20nor%20does%20it%20intend%20to%20fight%20for%20political%20office%20or%20intend%20to%20open%20diplomatic%20channels%20with%20Israel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20thing%20that%20is%20common%20between%20the%20two%20groups%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20both%20oppose%20Israel.%20Hamas%20and%20Islamic%20Jihad%20have%20often%20coordinated%20militant%20operations%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20enclave.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20have%20been%20times%20when%20Hamas%2C%20ironically%2C%20has%20cautioned%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20against%20attacking%20Israel.%20The%20Islamic%20Jihad%2C%20on%20most%20occasions%2C%20acts%20independently.%20Primarily%20focused%20on%20military%20confrontations%2C%20there%20have%20been%20times%20when%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20has%20taken%20the%20front%20seat%20while%20Hamas%20remained%20on%20the%20sidelines%20during%20clashes%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERelationship%20With%20Iran%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Iranian%20Revolution's%20sphere%20of%20influence%20in%20its%20first%20decade%20was%20confined%20to%20Shi'a%20groups%20in%20Iraq%2C%20Lebanon%2C%20and%20the%20Gulf%20Emirates.%20It%20failed%20to%20make%20headways%20in%20countries%20with%20a%20majority%20Sunni%20population%20nor%20did%20its%20fundamentalist%20ideas%20entice%20Islamic%20militant%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Shaqaqi%20and%20Awda%20drew%20inspiration%20from%20the%20Iranian%20Revolution%2C%20Iran%20did%20not%20pay%20it%20any%20heed.%20Ayatollah%20Khomenei%20and%20Iranian%20leaders%20remained%20steadfast%20in%20propagating%20Shi'ite%20values%20without%20focusing%20on%20Sunni-dominated%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20change%20occurred.%20In%20the%20late%2080s%2C%20after%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Iran-Iraq%20War%2C%20Iran%20decided%20to%20export%20its%20fundamentalism%20to%20countries%20like%20Egypt%2C%20Tunisia%2C%20Sudan%2C%20and%20more%20importantly%2C%20Palestine%20--%20coinciding%20with%20the%20First%20Intifada.%20And%20after%20Israel%20kicked%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%20to%20Lebanon%2C%20the%20group%20came%20under%20direct%20influence%20of%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20US%20State%20Department%2C%20it%20is%20Iran%20that%20funds%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad's%20budget%2C%20exactly%20like%20it%20reportedly%20does%20for%20Hamas%20and%20Hezbollah.%20The%20US%20also%20blames%20the%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20regime%20in%20Syria%20for%20providing%20a%20safe%20haven%20to%20the%20group%20in%20Damascus.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAttacks%20Carried%20Out%20By%20Islamic%20Jihad%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Islamic%20Jihad's%20modus%20operandi%20includes%20suicide%20bombings%20targetting%20Israeli%20civilians%20and%20military%20personnel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1987%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Killing%20Of%20an%20Israeli%20military%20police%20commander%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1994%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Car%20bomb%20attack%20killing%20nine%20and%20injuring%2050%20aboard%20a%20public%20bus%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1995%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Suicide%20bomb%20attack%20killing%2018%20soldiers%20and%20one%20civilian%20in%20ISrael's%20Netanya.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1996%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Suicide%20bomb%20attack%20at%20a%20Tel%20Aviv%20shopping%20mall%20killing%2013%20and%20injuring%2075.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2003%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Suicide%20bomb%20attack%20a%20a%20Haifa%20restaurant%20killing%2022%20and%20injuring%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlong%20w