20month%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Egyptian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.ahram.org.eg%2FNewsContent%2F1%2F1234%2F510287%2FEgypt%2FForeign-Affairs%2FEgyptian-MPs-condemn-Israeli-aggression-on-Gaza%2C-s.aspx%5C%22%3Emembers%20of%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DW3sDlhRckI0%5C%22%3Estate-owned%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20portrayed%20Israel%20as%20the%20aggressor%20and%20Hamas%20as%20the%20victim.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20accordance%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2022%2F4%2F26%2Fegypts-role-gaza-more-than-mediator%5C%22%3Epast%20actions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Egypt%20can%20be%20expected%20to%20take%20several%20steps%20to%20demonstrate%20its%20solidarity%20with%20the%20Palestinians.%20These%20include%3B%20the%20provision%20of%20humanitarian%20assistance%20to%20Gaza%2C%20evacuation%20of%20some%20wounded%20to%20Egyptian%20hospitals%2C%20and%20increased%20role%20in%20mediation%20efforts%20for%20a%20ceasefire.%20These%20steps%20make%20Egypt%20a%20key%20actor%20in%20the%20conflict%20and%20would%20help%20strengthen%20its%20regional%20and%20international%20standing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Egypt%20also%20doesn't%20want%20to%20alienate%20Israel.%20Ultimately%2C%20they%20have%20a%20mutual%20interest%3A%20they%20do%20not%20want%20to%20see%20the%20resurgence%20of%20political%20Islam%20in%20the%20region.%20This%20is%20linked%20to%20Egypt's%20own%20experience%20of%20Islamist%20organisations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20regime%20in%20Egypt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2013%2F07%2F04%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fegypt.html%5C%22%3Eousted%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%20in%202013%20and%20outlawed%20them.%20The%20Brotherhood%20is%20a%20transnational%20Islamist%20organisation%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cfr.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Fegypts-muslim-brotherhood%5C%22%3Efounded%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Egypt%20in%201928.%20It's%20aims%20are%20to%20promote%20social%20and%20political%20change%20in%20Muslim-majority%20countries.%20After%20the%20Arab%20Spring%20in%202011%2C%20the%20Brotherhood%20held%20power%20in%20Egypt%20for%20one%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2012%2F6%2F24%2Fcelebration-in-egypt-as-morsi-declared-winner%5C%22%3Ebefore%20being%20ousted%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHamas%20is%20an%20offspring%20of%20the%20Muslim%20Brotherhood%2C%20which%20is%20why%20Egypt%20perceives%20it%20as%20a%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20Egypt's%20suspicious%20approach%20to%20Hamas%2C%20since%202017%20there's%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.inss.org.il%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F01%2FGazaCrisis_ENG-129-140.pdf%5C%22%3Ean%20understanding%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%20two%3A%20Hamas'%20cooperation%20in%20fighting%20terrorism%20in%20Sinai%20would%20be%20met%20with%20an%20easing%20of%20the%20Egyptian%20blockade%20on%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20relations%20between%20Egypt%20and%20Israel%20are%20cooperative%2C%20they're%20not%20warm.%20Egypt%20signed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.state.gov%2Fmilestones%2F1977-1980%2Fcamp-david%5C%22%3Epeace%20agreement%20with%20Israel%20in%201979%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%2C%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Israel%20has%20positioned%20itself%20as%20a%20key%20political%2C%20security%20and%20economic%20partner%20to%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20Egypt%20has%20been%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2Fsada%2F85037%5C%22%3Emediator%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20and%20in%20the%20reconstruction%20efforts%20of%20Gaza.%20This%20is%20because%20of%20its%20proximity%20to%20Gaza%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20controls%20the%20Rafah%20crossing%20%E2%80%93%20the%20only%20border%20with%20the%20Gaza%20strip%20that's%20not%20under%20Israeli%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20Egypt's%20involvement%20with%20Gaza%20has%20certain%20lines%20that%20won't%20be%20crossed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20be%20no%20Egyptian%20military%20involvement%20against%20Israel%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20Palestinians%20%E2%80%93%20a%20policy%20which%20primarily%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fsecretary-antony-j-blinken-and-egyptian-president-abdel-fattah-el-sisi-before-their-meeting%2F%5C%22%3Ederives%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Egypt's%20commitment%20to%20the%201979%20peace%20agreement%20between%20Israel%20and%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20also%20be%20no%20sanctioned%20mass%20entry%20of%20Gazans%20into%20Egypt%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsis.gov.eg%2FStory%2F187293%2FSisi-Palestinians-must-%2527remain-on-their-land%2527%252C-contacts-ongoing-for-de-escalation-in-Gaza-war%3Flang%3Den-us%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%3C%2Fa%3E%20declarations%20by%20President%20Abdel%20Fattah%20el-Sisi%20and%20other%20Egyptian%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20the%20current%20crisis%20affect%20Egypt%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EEgypt%20has%20so%20far%20rejected%20the%20idea%20of%20displaced%20Palestinians%20moving%20into%20Sinai.%20But%20there%20is%20the%20possibility%20that%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Gazans%20will%20seek%20entry.%20This%20is%20separate%20to%20the%20Gaza%20residents%20with%20foreign%20citizenship%20who%20are%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Flive%2Fworld-middle-east-67119233%5C%22%3Ewaiting%20at%20the%20border%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20cross.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EEgypt%20is%20against%20allowing%20Gazans%20crossing%20the%20border%20in%20large%20numbers%20because%20it%20opposes%20any%20encroachment%20on%20its%20sovereignty%20in%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula.%20Its%20major%20concern%20is%20that%20displaced%20Palestinians%20may%20establish%20a%20permanent%20residence%20in%20its%20territory%2C%20potentially%20undermining%20the%20already%20delicate%20security%20and%20economic%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20also%20poses%20a%20large%20security%20risk%20to%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20border%20breaches%20by%20refugees%20from%20Gaza%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20may%20be%20armed%20individuals%20affiliated%20with%20Hamas%20or%20other%20radical%20groups%2C%20could%20export%20instability%20to%20Sinai.%20For%20Egypt%2C%20there%20is%20a%20danger%20that%20there%20could%20be%20more%20terrorist%20attacks%20and%20instability%20as%20there%20were%20in%20Sinai%20before%20the%202017%20understanding%20with%20Hamas.%20Some%20of%20those%20attacks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.euromesco.net%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2FEuroMeSCo36-Geopolitics-of-Violent-Extremism.-The-Case-of-Sinai.pdf%5C%22%3Ewere%20carried%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20well-armed%20and%20trained%20Gaza-based%20militant%20cells.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20a%20massive%20blow%20to%20Hamas%20may%20lead%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20governance%2C%20chaos%2C%20and%20instability%20in%20Gaza.%20This%20will%20cause%20instability%20and%20could%20give%20rise%20to%20the%20smuggling%20of%20weapons%20and%20fighters%20along%20Egypt's%20border%20with%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20security%20threat%20is%20that%20terrorist%20acts%20could%20be%20launched%20from%20Sinai%20into%20Israel%20by%20Palestinian%20militant%20groups%20putting%20the%20delicate%20relationship%20between%20Israel%20and%20Egypt%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20has%20Egypt%20reacted%20and%20what%20should%20it%20do%20next%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20outbreak%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Egypt%20has%20been%20working%20to%20de-escalate%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza%20and%20has%20been%20conducting%20talks%20with%20Israel%2C%20Hamas%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%2C%20the%20US%2C%20Iran%2C%20and%20other%20regional%20and%20international%20players.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Arab%20League%20has%20already%20convened%20in%20Cairo%2C%20and%20an%20international%20conference%20in%20Egypt%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20place%20this%20weekend.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F16%2Fegypts-tricky-calculation-as-israels-assault-on-gaza-continues%5C%22%3EEgypt%20is%20also%20seeking%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20establish%20a%20humanitarian%20corridor%20for%20the%20delivery%20of%20food%20and%20medicine%20to%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20stage%2C%20Egypt%20has%20more%20control%20than%20most%20other%20regional%20international%20players%20over%20the%20outcomes%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20as%20well%20as%20plenty%20of%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20outcome%20of%20the%20conflict%20could%20deliver%20some%20benefits.%20For%20example%2C%20Egypt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpost.com%2Fmiddle-east%2Farticle-745511%5C%22%3Edesires%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20return%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%2C%20who%20is%20more%20willing%20to%20engage%20in%20diplomacy%20and%20negotiations%2C%20as%20the%20governing%20authority%20in%20Gaza.%20A%20scenario%20where%20Hamas%20is%20significantly%20weakened%20could%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20new%20developments%2C%20possibly%20including%20the%20gradual%20return%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20Egypt%20and%20Israel%20could%20find%20a%20more%20pragmatic%20neighbour%20across%20their%20borders.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20Hamas%20loses%20power%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Egypt%20will%20most%20probably%20be%20involved%20in%20the%20government%20transition%20phase.%20As%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fhamas-abdel-fattah-el-sissi-middle-east-egypt-africa-e016845c51bf45d9652fbe41ed09dab6%5C%22%3Epast%20few%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Egypt%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20the%20conduit%20through%20which%20aid%20and%20funds%20from%20Arab%20countries%20and%20the%20international%20community%20will%20be%20transferred%20into%20Gaza%2C%20participate%20in%20its%20reconstruction%20process%2C%20and%20be%20a%20dominant%20influencing%20factor%20on%20shaping%20its%20future.%3Cimg%20r