515380.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EJordan%20has%20cancelled%20a%20summit%20with%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20leaders%20from%20Egypt%20and%20Palestine%20to%20discuss%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza.%20Jordan's%20Foreign%20Minister%20Ayman%20Safadi%20said%20the%20meeting%20would%20only%20be%20held%20when%20there%20is%20an%20agreement%20to%20end%20the%20violence%20against%20Palestinians.%20The%20cancellation%20of%20the%20summit%20reflects%20the%20volatile%20situation%20in%20the%20region%20as%20Biden%20visits%20Israel.%20The%20White%20House%20has%20stated%20that%20Biden%20postponed%20his%20visit%20to%20Jordan%20due%20to%20the%20explosion%20at%20a%20Gaza%20hospital.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fjordan-cancels-us-president-biden-summit-with-arab-leaders-after-gaza-hospital-blast%2Farticleshow%2F104515096.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20aims%20to%20send%20astronaut%20to%20the%20Moon%20by%202040%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697604725000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FAB1E%2Fproduction%2F_131460834_gettyimages-1531892466.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67142307%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20country's%20space%20goals%20also%20include%20include%20plans%20for%20a%20space%20station%20by%202035.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A59%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67142307%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67142307.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-67142307.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Judges%20Show%20Empathy%20With%20Queer%20Concerns%2C%20But%20Fail%20to%20Give%20Relief%20Citing%20Complexities%20Ahead%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F27115115%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_01.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20reading%20of%203%3A2%20366-page%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3ESupriyo%20%40%20Supriya%20Chakraborty%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmarriage-equality-supreme-court-decision%5C%22%3Epronounced%20by%20the%20five-judge%20Constitution%20bench%20on%20Tuesday%3C%2Fa%3E%20(October%2017)%2C%20shows%20that%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20case%20succeeded%20in%20securing%20empathy%2C%20if%20not%20justice%2C%20from%20the%20bench%2C%20to%20their%20prayers%20for%20recognition%20of%20the%20right%20to%20marriage%20equality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDoubtless%2C%20there%20was%20unanimity%20among%20the%20five%20judges%20on%20certain%20aspects.%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20authority%20to%20hear%20the%20case%20was%20one%20such.%20The%20second%20aspect%20is%20that%20queerness%20is%20a%20natural%20phenomenon%20that%20is%20neither%20urban%20nor%20elite.%20The%20third%20is%20that%C2%A0there%20exists%20no%20fundamental%20right%20to%20marry%20under%20the%20Constitution.%20Fourth%2C%20the%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20(SMA)%20is%20neither%20unconstitutional%20nor%20can%20be%20interpreted%20in%20such%20a%20manner%20so%20as%20to%20enable%20marriage%20between%20queer%20persons.%C2%A0%20Last%2C%20transgender%20persons%20in%20heterosexual%20relationships%20have%20the%20right%20to%20solemnise%20marriage%20under%20existing%20legal%20frameworks.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBeyond%20these%2C%20a%20distinction%20is%20discernible%20in%20the%20manner%20the%20majority%20and%20minority%20judges%20approached%20the%20issue.%20Justices%20Ravindra%20Bhat%20and%20Hima%20Kohli%20begin%20their%20judgment%20by%20observing%20that%20the%20task%20of%20the%20court%20lies%20in%20determining%20how%20the%20Constitution%20speaks%20on%20the%20issue.%20The%20five%20judges%20have%20no%20difficulty%20in%20agreeing%20that%20the%20Constitution%20aims%20at%20ending%20the%20discrimination%20suffered%20by%20the%20petitioners%20whose%20prayer%20is%20that%20the%20court%20should%20ensure%20their%20equality%20in%20marriage%20and%20not%20simply%20ask%20parliament%20to%20look%20into%20their%20grievances.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20exercise%20of%20granting%20appropriate%20and%20adequate%20relief%20to%20the%20petitioners%20appears%20to%20have%20forced%20all%20the%20five%20judges%20to%20throw%20in%20the%20towel.%20In%20this%2C%20the%20two%20minority%20judges%20failed%20to%20persuade%20the%20three%20majority%20judges%20to%20provide%20at%20least%20partial%20relief%20to%20the%20petitioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20prayer%20of%20the%20petitioners%20is%20that%20LGBTQ%2B%20persons%20be%20entitled%20to%20solemnise%20and%20register%20their%20marriages%20and%20claim%20their%20right%20to%20legal%20recognition%20of%20their%20unions%20within%20the%20marriage%20fold.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20five%20judges%20agreed%20that%20provisions%20of%20the%20SMA%20are%20incapable%20of%20being%20%E2%80%9Cread%20down%E2%80%9D%20or%20interpreted%20by%20%E2%80%9Creading%20up%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20manner%20suggested%20by%20the%20petitioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20the%20three%20majority%20judges%20agreed%20that%20reading%20down%20Section%204(c)%20of%20SMA%20and%20Sections%204(c)%20and%2017%20of%20the%20Foreign%20Marriage%20Act%2C%201969%20(FMA)%20and%20the%20notice%20and%20objection%20procedure%20under%20SMA%20can%20be%20decided%20by%20smaller%20benches%20because%20no%20question%20of%20law%20is%20involved%20in%20resolving%20this%20issue.%20Does%20this%20mean%20that%20the%20petitioners%20still%20can%20aspire%20for%20an%20efficacious%20remedy%20before%20smaller%20benches%20of%20this%20court%2C%20and%20relitigate%20some%20of%20these%20issues%2C%20left%20untouched%20by%20the%20larger%20bench%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20minority%20judges%E2%80%99%20worldview%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Justices%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20and%20S.K.%20Kaul%2C%20while%20there%20is%20no%20express%20fundamental%20right%20to%20marry%2C%20there%20is%20a%20right%20or%20freedom%20to%20enter%20into%20a%20union%20(spelt%20out%20in%20%3Cem%3ENavtej%20Johar%2C%20K.S.Puttaswamy%2C%20NALSA%2C%20Shakti%20Vahini%2C%20Shafin%20Jahan%20%3C%2Fem%3Eetc.)%20and%20our%20constitutional%20values%20entail%20respect%20to%20the%20choice%20of%20a%20person%20on%20entering%20into%20a%20marriage%20and%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20a%20marital%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20corollary%2C%20the%20two%20minority%20judges%20held%20that%20the%20right%20to%20union%20necessitates%20or%20places%20a%20positive%20obligation%20on%20the%20state%20to%20accord%20recognition%20to%20such%20relationships%2Funions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20majority%20judges%E2%80%99%20counterview%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20the%20three%20majority%20judges%2C%20however%2C%20there%20is%20indeed%20a%20right%20to%20relationship%20within%20Article%2021%20which%20includes%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20a%20partner%2C%20cohabit%20and%20enjoy%20physical%20intimacy%20with%20them%2C%20to%20live%20the%20way%20they%20wish%20to%2C%20and%20other%20rights%20that%20flow%20from%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%20autonomy%20and%20dignity.%20The%20state%2C%20however%2C%20is%20bound%20to%20extend%20necessary%20protection%20only%20when%20their%20right%20to%20enjoyment%20of%20such%20a%20relationship%20is%20under%20threat%20of%20violence%2C%20they%20clarified.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20positive%20obligation%20on%20the%20state%20to%20recognise%20this%20right%2C%20they%20held.%20The%20court%20cannot%20direct%20that%20the%20state%20must%20create%20a%20platform%20for%20this%20purpose%2C%20as%20that%20would%20be%20a%20stretch%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20overt%20or%20inert%20threat%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20the%20majority%20judges%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20one%20right%20can%20lead%20to%20other%20rights%2C%20emanating%20from%20it%2C%20has%20been%20conclusively%20rejected%20by%20seven%20judges%20in%20%3Cem%3EAll%20India%20Bank%20Employees%20Association%20v%20National%20Industrial%20Tribunal.%3C%2Fem%3E%20This%20decision%20was%20quoted%20with%20approval%20in%20%3Cem%3EManeka%20Gandhi%20v%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%20(The%20right%20to%20go%20abroad%20is%20clearly%20not%20a%20guaranteed%20right%20under%20any%20clause%20of%20Article%2019(1)).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20recorded%20instance%20nor%20was%20one%20pointed%20out%20where%20the%20court%20was%20asked%20to%20facilitate%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20social%20institution%20like%20in%20the%20present%20case%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20judgment%20authored%20by%20Justice%20Bhat%20and%20joined%20by%20Justice%20Kohli%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20judges%20termed%20CJI%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20previous%20observations%20in%20%3Cem%3ENavtej%20Johar%20%3C%2Fem%3Eas%20mere%20%3Cem%3Eobiter%20dicta.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20view%2C%20Justice%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20broader%20observations%20in%20%3Cem%3ENavtej%20Johar%3C%2Fem%3E%20obliging%20social%20institutions%20to%20accommodate%20and%20facilitate%20exercise%20of%20choice%20fully%20were%20not%20necessary.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20travelled%20beyond%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20remit%20and%20have%20to%20be%20viewed%20as%20obiter%20dicta.%20That%20the%20State%20should%20or%20ought%20to%20order%20such%20social%20institutions%2C%20is%20different%20from%20a%20%3Cu%3Edirection%3C%2Fu%3E%20issued%20by%20this%20court%2C%20which%20they%20%3Cem%3Emust%3C%2Fem%3E%20carry%20out%20(both%20underlined%20and%20italicised%20by%20Justice%20Bhat)%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Bhat%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20if%20we%20were%20to%2C%20for%20argument%20sake%2C%20recognise%20an%20entitlement%20under%20the%20Constitution%20to%20enter%20into%20an%20abiding%20cohabitational%20relationship%20or%20union%20%E2%80%93%20it%20cannot%20follow%20to%20a%20claim%20for%20an%20institution.%20There%20are%20almost%20intractable%20difficulties%20in%20creating%2C%20%3Cem%3Ethrough%20judicial%20diktat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%3Cu%3E%20a%20civil%20right%20to%20marry%20or%20a%20civil%20union%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%20no%20less%2C%20of%20the%20kind%20that%20is%20sought%20by%20the%20petitioners%20in%20these%20proceedings%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20majority%20judges%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COrdering%20a%20social%20institution%E2%80%9D%20or%20rearranging%20existing%20social%20structures%2C%20by%20creating%20an%20entirely%20new%20kind%20of%20parallel%20framework%20for%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20would%20require%20conception%20of%20an%20entirely%20different%20code%2C%20and%20a%20new%20universe%20of%20rights%20and%20obligations.%20This%20would%20entail%20fashioning%20a%20regime%20of%20state%20registration%2C%20of%20marriage%20between%20non-heterosexual%20couples%3B%20the%20conditions%20for%20a%20valid%20matrimonial%20relationship%20amongst%20them%2C%20spelling%20out%20eligibility%20conditions%2C%20such%20as%20minimum%20age%2C%20relationships%20which%20fall%20within%20%E2%80%9Cprohibited%20degrees%E2%80%9D%2C%20grounds%20for%20divorce%2C%20right%20to%20maintenance%2C%20alimony%20etc.%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20majority%20judges%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20nitty-gritty%20of%20providing%20relief%20to%20the%20petitioners%2C%20even%20as%20the%20majority%20judges%20empathised%20with%20their%20prayers%2C%20made%20them%20feel%20that%20this%20is%20beyond%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20present%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20elaboration%20of%20rights%20of%20queer%20persons%2C%20to%20say%20that%20exercise%20of%20choice%20to%20such%20relationships%20renders%20these%20rights%20meaningful%2C%20and%20that%20the%20state%20is%20obliged%20to%20%E2%80%9Crecognise%20a%20bouquet%20of%20entitlements%20which%20flow%20from%20such%20an%20abiding%20relationship%20of%20this%20kind%E2%80%9D%20is%20not%20called%20for%2C%20the%20majority%20judges%20explained%20their%20disagreement%20with%20the%20minority%20judges.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20judges%2C%20in%20the%20process%2C%20added%20many%20more%20reasons%2C%20not%20contemplated%20by%20the%20minority%20judges%2C%20to%20reject%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20prayer%20to%20read%20up%20the%20SMA.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20provisions%20and%20the%20objects%20of%20SMA%20clearly%20point%20to%20the%20circumstance%20that%20parliament%20intended%20only%20one%20kind%20of%20couples%2C%20i.e.%2C%20heterosexual%20couples%20belonging%20to%20different%20faiths%2C%20to%20be%20given%20the%20facility%20of%20a%20civil%20marriage%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EStructurally%2C%20Section%204%20(conditions%20relating%20to%20solemnisation%20of%20special%20marriages)%20contemplates%20marriages%20between%20a%20man%20and%20a%20woman.%20To%20read%20SMA%20in%20any%20other%20manner%20would%20be%20contrary%20to%20established%20principles%20of%20statutory%20interpretation.%C2%A0%20It%20is%20also%20not%20permissible%20for%20the%20court%20to%20%E2%80%98read%20up%E2%80%99%20and%20substitute%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98any%20two%20persons%E2%80%9D%20to%20refer%20to%20a%20marriage%20between%20non-heterosexual%20couples%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20purpose%20of%20terms%20like%20%E2%80%98wife%2C%20%E2%80%98husband%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98man%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98woman%E2%80%99%20in%20marriage%20laws%20(and%20other%20laws%20on%20sexual%20violence%20and%20harassment%20as%20well)%20is%20to%20protect%20a%20socially%20marginalised%20demographic%20of%20individuals.%20Provisions%20in%20the%20SMA%2C%20for%20alimony%2C%20and%20maintenance%20(Sections%2036%20and%2037)%20confer%20rights%20to%20women%3B%20likewise%20certain%20grounds%20of%20divorce%20(conviction%20of%20husband%20for%20bigamy%2C%20rape)%20entitle%20the%20wife%20additional%20grounds%20(Section%2027)%20to%20seek%20divorce%2C%20the%20majority%20judges%20explain.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20general%20pattern%20of%20these%20provisions%20%E2%80%93%20including%20the%20specific%20provisions%2C%20enabling%20or%20entitling%20women%20to%20certain%20benefits%2C%20and%20the%20effect%20of%20Sections%2019%2C%2020%2C%2021%20and%2021A%20of%20SMA%20is%20that%20even%20if%20for%20arguments%E2%80%99%20sake%2C%20it%20were%20accepted%20that%20Section%204%20of%20SMA%20could%20be%20read%20in%20gender%20neutral%20terms%2C%20the%20interplay%20of%20other%20provisions%20%E2%80%93%20which%20could%20apply%20to%20such%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20in%20such%20cases%2C%20would%20lead%20to%20anomalous%20results%2C%20rendering%20the%20SMA%20unworkable%2C%20they%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20wonders%20whether%20the%20petitioners%2C%20represented%20by%20a%20galaxy%20of%20senior%20counsel%2C%20were%20able%20to%20answer%20these%20concerns%20adequately%20during%20the%20hearing.%C2%A0%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20many%20of%20them%20conveyed%20their%20belief%20that%20a%20mere%20declaration%20by%20the%20court%20recognising%20their%20right%20to%20marriage%20equality%20would%20ensure%20resolution%20of%20such%20concerns%20in%20due%20course%20of%20time.%20But%20it%20appears%20that%20the%20judges%20%E2%80%93%20both%20majority%20and%20the%20minority%20%E2%80%93%20felt%20that%20the%20nitty-gritty%20ought%20to%20get%20precedence%20before%20a%20formal%20declaration%20from%20the%20court%20recognising%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20marriage%20equality%2C%20as%20it%20would%20only%20mean%20a%20mere%20lip%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20provisions%20of%20the%20SMA%20are%20to%20be%20construed%20as%20gender-neutral%20(such%20as%20persons%20or%20spouses%2C%20in%20substitution%20of%20wife%20and%20husband)%20it%20would%20be%20possible%20for%20a%20cis-woman%E2%80%99s%20husband%20to%20file%20a%20case%20or%20create%20a%20narrative%20to%20manipulate%20the%20situation.%20Gender-neutral%20interpretation%20of%20existing%20laws%2C%20therefore%2C%20would%20complicate%20an%20already%20exhausting%20path%20to%20justice%20for%20women%20and%20leave%20room%20for%20perpetrator%20to%20victimise%20them%2C%20says%20Justice%20Bhat%E2%80%99s%20judgment.%20Obviously%2C%20the%20majority%20judges%20seem%20to%20have%20been%20swayed%20by%20hypothetical%20situations%2C%20which%20can%20yield%20their%20own%20legal%20remedies%20when%20they%20actually%20happen%2C%20in%20declining%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWords%20of%20the%20statutes%20have%20to%20be%20read%2C%20taking%20into%20account%20the%20fabric%20of%20concepts%2C%20rights%2C%20obligations%20and%20remedies%20which%20it%20creates.%20Removing%20or%20decontextualising%20provisions%2C%20from%20their%20setting%20and%20%E2%80%9Cpurposively%E2%80%9D%20construing%20some%20of%20them%20cannot%20be%20resorted%20to%2C%20even%20in%20the%20case%20of%20SMA%20as%20well%20as%20FMA%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20majority%20judges%20reasoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmpathy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20judges%20agreed%20that%20not%20providing%20for%20non-heterosexual%20couples%20recognition%2C%20which%20is%20available%20for%20heterosexual%20couples%E2%80%99%20unions%20and%20cohabitation%20as%20marriages%20in%20various%20laws%20and%20regulations%2C%20results%20in%20their%20exclusion.%20They%20thus%20referred%20to%20employment%20(nominations%20in%20pension%2C%20provident%20fund%2C%20gratuity%2C%20life%20and%20personal%20accident%20insurance%20policies)%2C%20credit%2C%20purposes%20of%20receiving%20compensation%20in%20the%20event%20of%20fatal%20accidents%20as%20instances.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20individual%20earned%20benefits%20(by%20each%20partner%20or%20both%20collectively)%20which%20would%20be%20available%20to%20family%20members%20(such%20as%20employee%20state%20insurance%20benefits%2C%20in%20the%20event%20of%20injury%20of%20the%20earning%20partner%2C%20provident%20fund%2C%20compensation%2C%20medical%20benefits%2C%20insurance%20benefits%2C%20in%20the%20event%20of%20death%20of%20such%20earning%20partner)%20are%20examples%20of%20what%20the%20injured%20or%20deceased%20partner%20by%20dint%20of%20her%20or%20his%20work%2C%20becomes%20entitled%20to%2C%20or%20the%20members%20of%20her%20family%20become%20entitled%20to.%20The%20denial%20of%20these%20benefits%20and%20inability%20of%20the%20earning%20partner%20in%20a%20queer%20relationship%2C%20therefore%2C%20has%20an%20adverse%20discriminatory%20impact%2C%20they%20acknowledged.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20may%20not%20intend%20the%20discrimination%2C%20or%20exclusion%20in%20the%20conferment%20of%20such%20benefits%20or%20social%20welfare%20measures.%20Yet%2C%20the%20framework%20of%20such%20policies%20or%20regulations%2C%20expressed%20in%20favour%20of%20those%20in%20matrimonial%20relationships%2C%20results%20in%20denial%20of%20entitlements%2Fbenefits%2C%20despite%20the%20professional%20abilities%20and%20contributions%20which%20such%20individuals%20might%20make%20to%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20deprivation%20has%20to%20be%20addressed%2C%20the%20majority%20judges%20held.%20This%20injustice%20and%20inequity%20results%20in%20discrimination%2C%20unless%20remedial%20action%20is%20taken%20by%20the%20state%20and%20Central%20governments%2C%20they%20point%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20right%20to%20marry%20or%20have%20a%20legally%20recognised%20marriage%20is%20only%20statutory%2C%20the%20right%20to%20cohabit%20and%20live%20in%20a%20relationship%20in%20the%20privacy%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20home%20is%20fundamental%2C%20and%20enjoyed%20by%20all.%20This%20is%20not%20to%20say%20that%20the%20latter%20is%20unqualified%20or%20without%20restriction.%20Rather%20it%20is%20a%20right%20afforded%20to%20all%2C%20irrespective%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20recognition%20of%20the%20relationship%20or%20status%2C%20as%20in%20the%20case%20of%20married%20couples%2C%20the%20majority%20judges%20conceded.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20discriminatory%20impact%20recognised%20here%20is%20to%20highlight%20the%20effect%20of%20a%20legislative%20vacuum%20%E2%80%93%20specifically%20on%20long-term%20queer%20couples%2C%20who%20do%20not%20have%20the%20avenue%20of%20marriage%20to%20entitle%20them%20to%20earned%20benefits%2C%20they%20underlined.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECould%20this%20same%20logic%20then%20be%20extended%20to%20heterosexual%20couples%20that%20choose%20to%20not%20get%20married%2C%20despite%20having%20the%20avenue%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20judges%20underlined%20that%20this%20would%20require%20further%20consideration%20by%20the%20State%2C%20and%20was%20an%20aspect%20that%20was%20neither%20argued%2C%20nor%20were%20the%20judges%20called%20upon%20to%20decide%20in%20the%20present%20petitions.%20%E2%80%9CState%20must%20remain%20cognizant%20of%20such%20an%20unwitting%20consequence%20of%20creating%20two%20parallel%20frameworks%2C%20for%20live-in%20or%20domestic%20partnerships%2C%20and%20marriages%2C%20and%20the%20confusion%20or%20anomalies%20this%20may%20cause%20to%20gendered%20legal%20frameworks%20(as%20they%20stand%20today)%20while%20trying%20to%20remedy%20or%20mitigate%20the%20discrimination%20faced%20by%20queer%20couples%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20parliament%20has%20made%20the%20legislative%20choice%20of%20including%20only%20%E2%80%98married%E2%80%99%20couples%20for%20joint%20adoption%20(where%20two%20parents%20are%20legally%20responsible)%20arises%20from%20the%20reality%20of%20all%20other%20laws%20wherein%20protections%20and%20entitlements%20flow%20from%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20read%20down%20%E2%80%98marital%E2%80%99%20status%20as%20proposed%20may%20have%20deleterious%20impacts%20that%20only%20the%20legislature%20and%20executive%20could%20remedy%20%E2%80%93%20making%20this%2C%20much%20like%20the%20discussion%20on%20interpretation%20of%20SMA%2C%20an%20outcome%20that%20cannot%20be%20achieved%20by%20the%20judicial%20pen.%20Having%20said%20this%2C%20however%2C%20there%20is%20a%20discriminatory%20impact%20on%20queer%20couples%2C%20perhaps%20most%20visible%20through%20this%20example%20of%20adoption%20and%20its%20regulation%20that%20requires%20urgent%20state%20intervention%2C%20the%20majority%20judges%20acknowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20absence%20of%20legal%20recognition%20of%20a%20queer%20couple%20union%2C%20they%20are%20left%20to%20adopt%20as%20individuals%20and%20the%20resultant%3Cem%3E%20de%20facto%20%3C%2Fem%3Efamily%20would%20have%20no%20avenue%20for%20legal%20recognition.%20This%20iniquitous%20result%20too%20is%20an%20aspect%20which%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed%20as%20the%20impact%20here%20is%20not%20only%20on%20the%20queer%20couple%20(who%20have%20no%20avenue%20to%20seek%20legal%20recognition%20of%20their%20union)%20but%20also%20upon%20the%20children%20adopted%20by%20them%20(who%20have%20no%20say%20in%20the%20matter)%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20social%20reality%20that%20queer%20couples%20are%20having%20to%20adopt%20in%20law%20as%20individuals%2C%20but%20are%20residing%20together%20and%20for%20all%20purposes%20raising%20these%20children%20together%2C%20the%20State%20arguably%20has%20an%20even%20more%20urgent%20need%20to%20enable%20the%20full%20gamut%20of%20rights%20to%20such%20children%2C%20qua%20both%20parents%2C%20the%20majority%20judges%20highlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20underlying%20assumption%20in%20the%20law%20as%20it%20exists%20that%20such%20unmarried%20heterosexual%20or%20queer%20couples%20should%20not%20adopt%20needs%20to%20be%20closely%20examined.%20The%20need%20of%20such%20couples%20to%20have%20and%20raise%20a%20family%20in%20every%20sense%20of%20the%20term%2C%20has%20to%20be%20accommodated%20within%20the%20framework%20of%20the%20law%2C%20subject%20to%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20the%20child%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20have%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20existing%20state%20of%20affairs%20which%20permits%20single%20individuals%20to%20adopt%2C%20and%20later%20to%20live%20as%20a%20couple%20in%20due%20exercise%20of%20their%20choice%2C%20in%20effect%20deprives%20the%20children%20of%20such%20relationships%20various%20legal%20and%20social%20benefits%2C%20which%20are%20otherwise%20available%20to%20children%20of%20a%20married%20couple.%C2%A0%20The%20State%20as%20%3Cem%3Eparens%20patriae%20%3C%2Fem%3Eneeds%20to%20explore%20every%20possibility%20and%20not%20rule%20out%20any%20policy%20or%20legislative%20choice%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20maximum%20welfare%20and%20benefits%20reach%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20children%20in%20need%20of%20safe%20and%20secure%20homes%20with%20a%20promise%20for%20their%20fullest%20development%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20have%20recommended.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20judges%20identified%20their%20disagreement%20with%20the%20minority%20judges%20thus%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20court%20would%20have%20to%20fashion%20a%20parallel%20legal%20regime%2C%20comprising%20of%20defined%20entitlements%20and%20obligations.%20Such%20a%20framework%20containing%20obligations%20would%20cast%20responsibilities%20upon%20private%20citizens%20and%20not%20merely%20the%20State.%C2%A0%20The%20outlining%20of%20a%20bouquet%20of%20rights%20and%20indication%20that%20there%20is%20a%20separate%20constitutional%20right%20to%20union%20enjoyed%20by%20queer%20couples%2C%20with%20the%20concomitant%20obligation%20on%20the%20State%20to%20accord%20recognition%20to%20such%20union%2C%20is%20what%20we%20take%20exception%20to.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBy%20merely%20expecting%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20take%20the%20initiative%20and%20address%20the%20grievances%20of%20discrimination%20of%20the%20queer%20couples%20in%20specific%20areas%2C%20the%20majority%20judges%20seem%20to%20have%20missed%20an%20opportunity%20to%20at%20least%20make%20a%20beginning%2C%20and%20join%20the%20minority%20judges%20in%20meeting%20the%20aspirations%20of%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20persons%20to%20the%20extent%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697603955000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F27115115%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_01.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-judges-show-empathy-with-queer-concerns-but-fail-to-give-relief-citing-complexities-ahead%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Justices%20S.%20Ravindra%20Bhat%2C%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20P.S.%20Narasimha%20differed%20from%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20and%20Justice%20S.K.%20Kaul%20on%20moulding%20relief%20to%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20marriage%20equality%20case%20because%20they%20found%20the%20means%20adopted%20by%20the%20latter%20were%20not%20%E2%80%9Clegally%20sound%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-judges-show-empathy-with-queer-concerns-but-fail-to-give-relief-citing-complexities-ahead%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Close%20coordination%20with%20China%20crucial%20in%20a%20difficult%20world%3A%20Vladimir%20Putin%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697603803000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104514342%2Cimgsize-28210.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fclose-coordination-with-china-crucial-in-a-difficult-world-vladimir-putin%2Farticleshow%2F104514221.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104514221.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fclose-coordination-with-china-crucial-in-a-difficult-world-vladimir-putin%2Farticleshow%2F104514221.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fwor